name: BMO Ultra Short-Term Bond ETF
longDescription: The ETF seeks to provide exposure to a variety of fixed income securities with a remaining effective term to maturity of one year or less. The ETF will primarily invest in money market instruments and directly in fixed income securities, including corporate, Government of Canada, provincial and municipal bonds. The ETF may invest in floating rate instruments, floating rate preferred shares and other floating rate securities, subject to the rate reset date being no greater than one year and the term being no greater than five years.
